messageBody:
mirumoto_kojiro wrote:
> I'm confused over this message from a junit test. I'm using
> assertEquals(String,String,String). The message is printing out the
> expected and the accual. As you can see they are identical. I
> expect 200D-CL7-116 and get 200D-CL7-116. I've tried trim() on my
> output but still the error.
>
> junit.framework.ComparisonFailure: Lot should be 200D-CL7-116 and is
> 200D-CL7-166 expected:<...1...> but was:<...6...>
>
> Any ideas of what to look for? Is is comparing Objects and not
> Strings?

The strings are different. Look again: the "actual" value ends in 166,
and not 116.
